        "description": "## GET All Tasks\n\nRetrieves all tasks stored in the system. Use this endpoint to fetch the complete list of tasks.\n\n**Method:** `GET`\n**URL:** `{{baseURL}}/tasks`\n\n---\n\n### Response Format\n\nReturns a JSON array of task objects. Each task object contains the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `id` | number | Unique identifier for the task |\n| `title` | string | The title/name of the task |\n| `completed` | boolean | Whether the task has been completed |\n\n---\n\n### Example Response\n\n**Status:** `200 OK`\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"title\": \"Update Jira tickets\",\n    \"completed\": false\n  }\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n### Notes\n\n- The base URL is stored in the `baseURL` environment variable (configured in the **Task Tracker Environment**). Make sure the correct environment is selected before sending this request.\n- A `200 OK` status code indicates a successful response.\n"
      },
      "response": [
        {
          "name": "200 OK",
          "originalRequest": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseURL}}/tasks",
              "host": [
                "{{baseURL}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "tasks"
              ]
            }
