        "description": "## POST New Task\n\nCreates a new task in the system. Use this endpoint to add a task with the relevant details.\n\n**Method:** `POST`  \n**URL:** `{{baseURL}}/tasks`\n\n---\n\n### Request Body\n\nSend a JSON object in the request body with the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `title` | `string` | The title of the task |\n| `description` | `string` | A detailed description of the task |\n| `status` | `string` | The current status (e.g. `pending`, `in-progress`, `completed`) |\n| `dueDate` | `string` | The due date for the task (ISO 8601 format) |\n| `priority` | `string` | Priority level (e.g. `low`, `medium`, `high`) |\n\n**Example request body:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Fix login bug\",\n  \"description\": \"Investigate and resolve the login issue on the auth page\",\n  \"status\": \"pending\",\n  \"dueDate\": \"2024-12-31\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Response Format\n\nReturns the newly created task object with a `201 Created` status code.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"abc123\",\n  \"title\": \"Fix login bug\",\n  \"description\": \"Investigate and resolve the login issue on the auth page\",\n  \"status\": \"pending\",\n  \"dueDate\": \"2024-12-31\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-06-01T10:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Notes\n\n- The `Content-Type` header should be set to `application/json`.\n- The `id` and `createdAt` fields are generated by the server and should not be included in the request body.\n- Use `{{baseURL}}` as the base URL variable, configured in your active environment."
      },
